com.gwtplatform.mvp.rebind
Class GinjectorInspector

java.lang.Object
  com.gwtplatform.mvp.rebind.GinjectorInspector

public class GinjectorInspector
extends Object

This class is used to inspect the user-provided ginjector. This is typically useful to identify 'get' methods that generate specific types. You must call init() before any other method can be called.

Author:
Philippe Beaudoin

findGetMethod

public String findGetMethod(JClassType returnType)
                     throws UnableToCompleteException
Looks at the ginjector methods to find one that return the specified type. The get method can be either in the ginjector or any of its parent class.

Parameters:
returnType - The type that should be returned by the get method.
Returns:
The get method returning returnType<returnTypeParameter>, or null if not found.
Throws:
UnableToCompleteException - If more than one matching method is found.

findGetMethod

public String findGetMethod(JGenericType returnType,
                            JClassType returnTypeParameter)
                     throws UnableToCompleteException
Looks at the ginjector methods to find one that return the specified parameterized type with the specified type as a parameter. The get method can be either in the ginjector or any of its parent class.

Parameters:
returnType - The parameterized type that should be returned by the get method.
returnTypeParameter - The type parameter of returnType.
Returns:
The get method returning returnType<returnTypeParameter>, or null if not found.
Throws:
UnableToCompleteException - If more than one matching method is found.

findAnnotatedGetMethod

public String findAnnotatedGetMethod(JClassType returnType,
                                     Class<? extends Annotation> annotation,
                                     boolean failIfAnnotationIsFoundOnWrongMethod)
                              throws UnableToCompleteException
Looks at the ginjector methods to find one that return the specified type and that is annotated with the specified annotation. The get method can be either in the ginjector or any of its parent class.

Parameters:
returnType - The type that should be returned by the get method.
annotation - The annotation that should be present on the get method.
failIfAnnotationIsFoundOnWrongMethod - If true, the call will throw an UnableToCompleteException and log an error if the annotation is found on the wrong method.
Returns:
The get method returning returnType and annotated with annotation, or null if not found.
Throws:
UnableToCompleteException - If more than one matching method is found.
